Package animals

Class Animal

java.lang.Object
farm.FarmItem
animals.Animal
Direct Known Subclasses:
Chicken, Cow, Sheep
public abstract class Animal
extends FarmItem
Logic and structure superclass to construct different animals.

This class provides each animal with the logic and structure required, by expanding on the FarmItem structure.
Animals function as a daily income (rewarded at endDay()) and require feeding and playing with to keep health and mood high.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Alex Burling(arb142)
See Also:
FarmItem, * @see Cow, Sheep

    • Animal

      public Animal​(java.lang.String name, java.lang.String description, float price, float dailyProfit, float health, float mood, FarmItem.FarmItems selfEnum)
      Constructs the Animal from the FarmItem constructor and animal specific values (dailyProfit, health, mood)
      Parameters:
      name - Animal's name, e.g. Cow, Chicken etc
      description - Animal's description, only shown when viewing status of animal
      price - Animal's price, used when buying or selling to store
      dailyProfit - Animal's daily profit, used when calculating the income from each animal (along with health and mood)
      health - Animal's base health, deteriorates daily, used when calculating the income from each animal
      mood - Animal's base mood, deteriorates daily, used when calculating the income from each animal
      selfEnum - holds the enum representing the object for easier cloning

    • endDay

      public void endDay()
      Handles end of the day actions for Animal objects

      Every FarmItem subclass must implement an endDay() function, to simplify game loop. This is to handle animal specific logic and attributes.
      i.e. deteriorates health and mood, which drop at constant value, and adds profit.
      However mood will deteriorate faster when low health, and animal will die/run away on 0.
      Profit earned at the end of each day is dependent on health, mood, and internal value.

      Specified by:
      endDay in class FarmItem

    • feed

      public void feed()
      Updates object attributes consistent with feeding the animal as a daily action

      This function takes no parameters, and acts as standard feeding. i.e. increases animal health at no cost.
      To feed with a health item, call with Item as parameter (feed(Item))

    • feed

      public void feed​(Item item) throws InvalidItemException
      Updates object attributes consistent with feeding the animal with an item as a daily action.

      This function takes one item, to be consumed. i.e. increases animal health multiplied by item modifier (Item.getMod())
      To feed without a health item, call without Item as parameter (feed())

      Parameters:
      item - FarmItem to use while feeding
      Throws:
      InvalidItemException - if (Item.getEffect()) != "health"

    • play

      public void play()
      Updates object attributes consistent with playing with the animal as a daily action

      This function takes no parameters, and acts as standard playing. i.e. increases animal mood at no cost.
      To play with a mood item, call with Item as parameter (play(Item))
